This paper is about explaining decisions made by AI systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of AI and machine learning (cs.AI) and specifically, the subfield of explainable AI. The paper also discusses the use of feature importance weights, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of scalability, which is relevant to the field of computational engineering (cs.CE). The paper also discusses the importance of context in selecting the most useful explanations, which is relevant to the field of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of current methods for explaining model predictions, which is relevant to the field of computer security (cs.CR).
